    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html lang="en" data-theme="winter">

    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <title>About - LGS</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/main.css">
    </head>

    <body>
        <%- include('../partials/navbar') %>

            <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-4xl">
                <div class="mb-12 text-center">
                    <h1 class="text-4xl font-black tracking-tight mb-4">About the System</h1>
                    <div class="w-24 h-1 bg-primary mx-auto rounded-full"></div>
                </div>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8">
                    <div class="card bg-white border border-base-200 shadow-sm overflow-hidden text-lg">
                        <div class="card-body p-8 sm:p-12 prose prose-slate max-w-none">
                            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Laptop Grading System (LGS)</h2>
                            <p>
                                Laptop Grading System (LGS) is a lightweight web application designed to standardize
                                laptop
                                grading during the refurbishment workflow. It replaces scattered individual spreadsheets
                                with a single, consistent process for capturing key device information—model and brand
                                details, battery health, condition notes, and technician observations—in a way that is
                                easy
                                to use and simple to audit.
                            </p>

                            <h3
                                class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 border-l-4 border-secondary pl-4 text-secondary-focus">
                                Why LGS exists</h3>
                            <p>
                                In many refurb environments, grading is done in separate Excel files maintained by each
                                technician. Over time, this leads to inconsistent formats, duplicated effort, missing
                                details, and difficulty generating reliable summaries. LGS was created to bring grading
                                into
                                one shared system with a consistent structure and clearer traceability.
                            </p>

                            <h3
                                class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 border-l-4 border-secondary pl-4 text-secondary-focus">
                                Key benefits</h3>
                            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
                                <li><strong>Standardized grading:</strong> one format for everyone, reducing
                                    inconsistencies
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Better traceability:</strong> entries are easier to review and follow over
                                    time
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Faster handoff:</strong> cleaner information for QA, inventory, or
                                    downstream
                                    steps</li>
                                <li><strong>Foundation for reporting:</strong> enables future dashboards and exports
                                    with
                                    consistent data</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h3
                                class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 border-l-4 border-secondary pl-4 text-secondary-focus">
                                Tech overview</h3>
                            <p>
                                LGS is built with <strong>Node.js + Express</strong>, <strong>EJS</strong> server-side
                                rendering, <strong>PostgreSQL</strong>, and <strong>Tailwind CSS/DaisyUI</strong> for a
                                clean internal-tool UI. It uses session-based authentication and secure password
                                hashing.
                            </p>

                            <h3
                                class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4 border-l-4 border-secondary pl-4 text-secondary-focus">
                                Open source & contributions</h3>
                            <p>
                                This project is open source and evolves based on real workflow needs. Suggestions and
                                contributions are welcome, especially improvements that make grading faster, clearer,
                                and
                                more consistent for technicians.
                            </p>

                            <div class="divider mt-12 mb-8"></div>

                            <div
                                class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4 text-sm opacity-60">
                                <div>
                                    <strong>Credits:</strong> Created and maintained by Hiran Tiago Lins Borba
                                </div>
                                <div class="badge badge-outline">2025-2026</div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="mt-12 text-center">
                    <a href="/" class="btn btn-ghost">
